<subSubSection id="C379979F16343676AE09FA49DDC43544" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BDCC41416343676AE09FA49DDC43544" blockId="15.[794,1417,1530,1619]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis id="B917180616343676AE09FA49DDA43504" bold="true" box="[794,929,1530,1555]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Etymology:</emphasis>
The specific epithet 
<taxonomicName id="4C63BF9716343676A982FA49DAF13504" authorityName="Biffi &amp; Geiser" authorityYear="2020" box="[1169,1268,1530,1555]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Peltariosilis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orientalis">
<emphasis id="B917180616343676A982FA49DAF13504" box="[1169,1268,1530,1555]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">orientalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
refers to the distribution of the species, in the easternmost reaches of Amazon forest.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
